headlines.description: — When the Milwaukee Bucks needed a steadying presence Friday night at Indiana, Giannis Antetokounmpo provided it — even from the free-throw line.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 41 points, Bucks beat Pacers 141-131

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 13 of his 25 points in the third quarter as Minnesota extended its lead, D’Angelo Russell added 19 points and the Timberwolves topped the short-handed Memphis Grizzlies 111-100 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves top Memphis after moment of silence for Nichols

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo has a theory. All these close games that the Miami Heat are playing now, in his mind, are providing valuable lessons to draw upon later this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat rally again, top Magic 110-105 to close 3-0 homestand

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 35 points, his fourth consecutive game with at least 30, and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 112-100 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander has 35, leads Thunder past Cavs 112-100

events.name: Toronto Raptors at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry had 35 points and 11 assists, and the Golden State Warriors beat the Toronto Raptors 129-117 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry's 35 points send Warriors past Raptors, 129-117
